transcript.text: Hello, welcome to on print shop.
This video is about admin group roles.
In this video the first one is what are the admin group roles and what are super admins and sub admins.
So inside the admin panel if you want to give the access of admin to your employees or some other person, you can create them as a super admin or as a sub admin.
Super admin means he will have all the access of the admin banner and sub admin means he will have limited access.

To give the limited access, first we need to define the role and then once we assign, once we create the role then we can assign it to the person so he can use the admin panel but with the limited access only.
So let's see how we can create the admin roles and how we can create the Super admins and sub admins and how the admin panel look like for super admins and sub admins.
Go to the admin.
So here in the admin, the last module is admin where there are two things.
One is this admin and 1 is this group roles.
So first of all, we need to define the group roles.
Let's say if we create one group where we are giving it to a marketing team.

So what we are creating, we are creating let's say for marketing person, we are creating this group for marketing person where we are giving them the access of products, we are giving them the access of content management, we are giving them the access of SEO's they can manage.
OK.
So there are only three modules which we are giving them the access then just save it.

So as we will created as we have created this marketing person group, OK, so here you can see the group rules marketing person that will be available where they can have access only for a few things products, SU and content management.
Now we need to assign this marketing person to the marketing person.
So for that we will go into the admin here just click on add button and here default store.
Then the role which role you want to assign them, the marketing person role.
Then the username.
Let's say if I will take mine so I am taking at 632166321.
I am creating a password.
So here I am taking my e-mail ID this dummy one.
Then if you will click on super admin.
So what does super admin means?
Like you have the entire access, this person will have the entire access of the entire admin panel.
But if you are creating it, a sub admin status should be active notify.
If you activate the notify, the customer will sorry.
This person will receive the username and password on his e-mail ID.
That's it.
So let's say we are just end status admin.
So now this person when this person only login into the admin.
So let's say the admin URL will remain same if you click over here login as admin for how this admin will look like of this sub admin this is we term as a sub admin.
So here is the sub admins.
You can see the dashboard product part contain management and SEO.
Only three things we have assigned and they can access only three things.
They will not be able to access any other thing apart from these three things.
So that's how you can create group roles and you can assign the group roles to the particular person or particular team so they can have the limited access.
If you have any queries and concerns, please connect with us at support at on printshop.com.
Thank you.
